OL,3,C'I blame the Post Office for my
OL,4,Chusband's death': Widow speaks out
OL,6,FThere is an obvious implication, so I
OL,7,Fask her: "Is it possible that he did
OL,8,Ftake the money?"
OL,10,F"I don't think so," she replies.
OL,12,FThe truth is there's no proof, only
OL,13,Funanswered questions.
OL,15,FEven the Post Office has conceded that
OL,16,Fthere is no Horizon transaction data
OL,17,Ffor Jayakanthan's branch and only
OL,18,Flimited relevant documents in a case
OL,19,Fthat cost a man his life.
